wikipedia_page.main: David James (3 June 1791 – 1 May 1846) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) who was active in the 1810s. James, who was born in Marylebone, is recorded in two matches, totalling 11 runs with a highest score of 9. He held two catches and took 3 wickets including one return of 4 wickets in an innings. He died in Lincolns Inn, London, aged 54.
